ManagedInstance

public ManagedInstance(String name,
                       String instanceType,
                       String imageID,
                       String locationID,
                       String publicKey,
                       Map parms)

Title: ManagedInstance that has information to deploy

Description: initialize an instance that doesn't exist , pass parameters that need to create instance .

Parameters:
name - name of the instance
instanceType - instance type such as COP64.2/4096/60, find more in User Guide.
imageID - the image id that this instance launched from.
locationID - the location where run this instane .
publicKey - a ssh key name that created in SCE account.this key will later be used to connect to instance.
parms - a map that contains configuration parameters
See Also:
ManagedLocation

capture

public com.ibm.cloud.api.rest.client.bean.Image capture(String imageName,
                                                        String imageDesc)
                                                 throws ManagedInstanceException

Title: capture

Description:Saves the Instance to a new private Image with the specified name and description. The new image will take a finite time to create. Wait for the image to change to an AVAILABLE state before using the image to create an instance from. During this time the state of the instance will change to CAPTURING.

Parameters:
imageName - image name
imageDesc - image description
Returns:
Image
Throws:
ManagedInstanceException
See Also:
Image
